# Time Awareness (Dan standing preference)

## Time constraints (summary)

- **Users are always time-bound** — track stated windows; re-estimate after each ship cycle.
- **Budget filter** — only offer **Fits now** / **To continue** when `budget ≤ remaining` (see **Time estimate calibration**).
- **No out-of-budget CTAs** — out-of-budget items → **Save for later** only.
- **Remaining time options** — mandatory after successful ship when a window was stated.
- **Active default** — overnight/away-batch execute only on explicit sleep/overnight trigger.

## Session mode fork (mandatory — early in substantive sessions)

Before implement/ship work, confirm **how Dan wants to work** — unless mode already stated. Ask **one** question when unclear: **A) Active now** (interactive ship-as-we-go) vs **B) Away planning** (rank/queue, draft away-NNN, wait for **"go build it"**).

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| Explicit mode | "active now", "away-style planning", "just plan" → **skip re-ask** |
| Away planning ≠ overnight | Plan → Approve → Queue anytime; **`npm run away:plan`** only; no `away-list.json` write; no `away:batch` until Dan approves |
| Active now | Normal implement → verify → ship |
| After approval | Plan → Approve → Queue → Execute — `AWAY_BUILD_PROTOCOL.md`, `composer-orchestrator.mdc` |

No sleep/overnight framing when Dan chose away planning during daytime.

## Infer time & stated window

Anchor on **`user_info` "Today's date"**; trust Dan's cues over stale overnight framing. On deadline/window (`until 6:15`, `30 more minutes`): **record** (clock or duration), **re-estimate** after each ship cycle, **replace** (don't stack) if Dan changes mid-session.

## Session pacing

Morning/day without sleep language → active work; no default overnight framing; check-in → `CURRENT_STATE.md`. Overnight/sleep triggers only → Plan → Approve → Queue → Execute (`composer-orchestrator.mdc`, `AWAY_BUILD_PROTOCOL.md`). Early AM → brief greeting + **session mode fork** unless mode chosen. Evening + sleep → default **B)** if sleep mentioned. "Morning after batch" = daytime mode (Dan awake).

## Time estimate calibration

Heuristics — calibrate from actuals. Present **Budget** (conservative filter) + **Typical** (expected elapsed).

| Category | Budget | Typical |
|----------|--------|---------|
| Verify-only scripts (bundle) | 10–15 min | 1–3 min (often <2 min) |
| `verify:pickup:prod` alone | 15 min | ~1 min |
| T1 single-domain ship (e.g. Settings UI) | 35 min | 20–25 min |
| T1 ui polish (drawer copy, table row, modal) | 15 min | ~6 min |
| T1 verify harness script | 35 min | 15–25 min |
| T3 CF + Sonnet + deploy | 50 min | 35–45 min |

- Filter on **budget only** — never offer if `budget > remaining`; typical informational.
- After ship/verify with stated window → note **actual elapsed**; away ships cite `estimate-log.md`.
- Away ships: `task-start`/`task-finish` → `estimate-log.md`; `actualElapsedMin` from timestamps; `timingSource: worker_reported_timestamps`; unknown when not recorded; **`npm run estimate:audit`** every 15 rows.
- Prefer npm script names over vague estimates.

## Time-bound suggestions (mandatory)

Hard budget on remaining minutes. Before actionable suggestions: estimate with **budget**, compare to **remaining**, include in Fits now/To continue only when `budget ≤ remaining`, never ask for unaffordable work, never present out-of-budget as actionable (no hypotheticals unless Dan updates window). Out-of-budget → **Save for later** only (name + estimate; no CTA). Filter before present.

## Remaining time options (post-ship — mandatory)

After successful ship within stated window → **Remaining time options** section + **actual elapsed** (away: `estimate-log.md` row). Include when: window stated, task succeeded, remaining **> 0**.

**Format:** `### Remaining time options` — **~N min left**; **Fits now:** (2–3 ranked, `budget ≤ remaining` only, or nothing shippable); **Save for later:** (out-of-budget, no CTA); **To continue:** (in-budget only; omit or "quick verify only or stop").

**Rank:** (1) `away-list.json` / `npm run away:next` — no invented ids; (2) cross-check `CURRENT_STATE.md`, blockers, scope; (3) calibration table; (4) drop over-budget from Fits now/To continue; (5) no overnight/`away:plan` hypotheticals in active window; (6) away planning → approve candidates, **"go build it"** before batch.

**Skip:** deadline passed; no window (skip or ask once); remaining unknown (omit or ask once).
